<TEI xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" xmlns:frus="http://history.state.gov/frus/ns/1.0"><text><body><div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1925-06-16T21:00:00-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1925-06-16T21:00:00-05:00" n="515" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d515">
                        <note rend="inline" type="source">893.00/6285: Telegram</note>
                        <head><hi rend="italic">The Ambassador in Japan</hi> (<persName type="from"><hi rend="italic">Bancroft</hi></persName>) <hi rend="italic">to the <gloss type="to">Secretary of State</gloss></hi></head>
                        <opener><dateline rendition="#right"><placeName><hi rend="smallcaps">Tokyo</hi></placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1925-06-17T11:00:00+09:00"><hi rend="italic">June 17,
                                        1925—11 a.m.</hi></date><lb/>[Received June 17—8:55
                                a.m.]</dateline></opener>
                        <p>112. Your telegram to Peking number 107, June 13 [<hi rend="italic">12</hi>], 5 p.m. Last evening I conveyed purport to Foreign
                            Minister who expressed gratification.</p>
                        <closer><signed><hi rend="smallcaps">Bancroft</hi></signed></closer>
